r4428 | dbera | 2008-01-27 20:11:53 -0500 (Sun, 27 Jan 2008) | 2 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/beagle/firefox-extension/README
   M /trunk/beagle/firefox-extension/chrome/content/beagleOverlay.xul
   A /trunk/beagle/firefox-extension/chrome/content/beagleSearch.js
   A /trunk/beagle/firefox-extension/chrome/content/sidebar.xul
   M /trunk/beagle/firefox-extension/chrome/locale/en-US/beagle.dtd
   A /trunk/beagle/firefox-extension/chrome/skin/classic/sidebar.css

It does not make sense if apps can only submit data for indexing but cannot search in the submitted data. Add a simple sidebar to search the indexed webpages and bookmarks. libbeagle requires a glib mainloop to run and I am not sure firefox allows another mainloop right now, so instead use the webinterface. As a side-effect, if you enable NetworkService backend then you can search your webhistory and bookmarks from anywhere in the internet (this is kind of scary, I have to remember to disable indexing certain pages from now on).

------------------------------------------------------------------------
